1
00:01:37,080 --> 00:01:40,130
[Born to Be Alive]

2
00:01:40,150 --> 00:01:43,220
[Episode 7]

3
00:01:44,759 --> 00:01:45,710
No way.

4
00:01:46,900 --> 00:01:47,420
This is bad.

5
00:01:47,420 --> 00:01:48,039
No, no.

6
00:01:48,140 --> 00:01:49,070
Captain Duojie!

7
00:01:49,430 --> 00:01:50,539
Captain Duojie!

8
00:01:51,060 --> 00:01:51,789
Captain!

9
00:01:54,000 --> 00:01:54,650
Captain.

10
00:01:55,930 --> 00:01:56,860
Captain Duojie!

11
00:01:56,970 --> 00:01:58,229
What's wrong with him?

12
00:01:58,590 --> 00:01:59,280
A sugar rush?

13
00:01:59,280 --> 00:02:00,330
Go to sleep!

14
00:02:00,500 --> 00:02:01,790
Captain, open the door.

15
00:02:01,790 --> 00:02:02,620
Coming.

16
00:02:05,140 --> 00:02:05,710
Captain,

17
00:02:06,340 --> 00:02:07,620
I need to talk to you.

18
00:02:07,780 --> 00:02:08,180
Okay.

19
00:02:08,840 --> 00:02:10,000
Come inside. Calm down.

20
00:02:10,000 --> 00:02:10,600
I'm sorry

21
00:02:10,630 --> 00:02:11,370
to disturb you,

22
00:02:11,370 --> 00:02:11,810
but

23
00:02:11,910 --> 00:02:12,340
I have to

24
00:02:12,340 --> 00:02:12,870
talk to you

25
00:02:12,870 --> 00:02:14,000
about this tonight.

26
00:02:16,530 --> 00:02:17,130
I know

27
00:02:17,170 --> 00:02:18,570
your anti-poaching work

28
00:02:19,000 --> 00:02:19,780
and protection of Tibetan antelopes

29
00:02:19,780 --> 00:02:20,230
is very tough

30
00:02:20,230 --> 00:02:21,090
and admirable.

31
00:02:21,130 --> 00:02:22,590
But have you done the math?

32
00:02:22,840 --> 00:02:24,170
At Zhuoyuan Lake alone,

33
00:02:24,590 --> 00:02:25,500
within one year,

34
00:02:25,500 --> 00:02:26,710
you cracked at least five cases.

35
00:02:26,710 --> 00:02:27,310
On average,

36
00:02:27,310 --> 00:02:28,320
there were over 200

37
00:02:28,320 --> 00:02:30,000
Tibetan antelope carcasses each time.

38
00:02:30,000 --> 00:02:30,970
That's 1,000 already.

39
00:02:30,970 --> 00:02:32,030
Among these 1,000,

40
00:02:32,060 --> 00:02:32,900
a large proportion

41
00:02:32,900 --> 00:02:34,030
were pregnant females.

42
00:02:34,030 --> 00:02:35,250
You mentioned in your notes

43
00:02:35,250 --> 00:02:36,250
that Tibetan antelopes usually

44
00:02:36,250 --> 00:02:37,930
give birth to only one calf at a time.

45
00:02:37,930 --> 00:02:38,790
Adding in these

46
00:02:38,800 --> 00:02:39,870
unborn calves,

47
00:02:40,210 --> 00:02:41,120
from your cases alone,

48
00:02:41,120 --> 00:02:42,340
in one year, 1,500

49
00:02:42,360 --> 00:02:43,460
to 2,000 Tibetan antelopes

50
00:02:43,460 --> 00:02:44,180
were killed.

51
00:02:44,180 --> 00:02:44,740
Plus

52
00:02:44,840 --> 00:02:45,870
the pelts seized

53
00:02:45,950 --> 00:02:47,600
where no carcasses were found,

54
00:02:47,600 --> 00:02:48,960
I'd conservatively double that,

55
00:02:48,960 --> 00:02:50,300
making it 3,000 to 4,000.

56
00:02:50,300 --> 00:02:51,710
That's merely what was seized.

57
00:02:51,710 --> 00:02:52,520
What you didn't see,

58
00:02:52,520 --> 00:02:53,810
I'll estimate at 1,000.

59
00:02:53,810 --> 00:02:54,250
In just one year,

60
00:02:54,250 --> 00:02:55,270
5,000 Tibetan antelopes

61
00:02:55,270 --> 00:02:56,000
were killed.

62
00:02:56,900 --> 00:02:58,400
The Bolamula region

63
00:02:58,500 --> 00:03:00,270
spans Qinghai, Tibet

64
00:03:00,300 --> 00:03:01,080
and Xinjiang.

65
00:03:01,080 --> 00:03:01,610
There're

66
00:03:01,620 --> 00:03:02,300
about 10 major habitats

67
00:03:02,300 --> 00:03:03,020
for Tibetan antelopes.

68
00:03:03,020 --> 00:03:03,620
If I assume

69
00:03:03,650 --> 00:03:04,710
half of these areas

70
00:03:04,740 --> 00:03:06,180
are experiencing similar poaching,

71
00:03:06,180 --> 00:03:07,190
that means five times

72
00:03:07,190 --> 00:03:08,780
the rate of population decline.

73
00:03:08,780 --> 00:03:09,840
And the population

74
00:03:09,940 --> 00:03:10,760
of Tibetan antelopes

75
00:03:10,760 --> 00:03:12,150
recovers very slowly.

76
00:03:12,210 --> 00:03:13,940
According to your statistics,

77
00:03:14,080 --> 00:03:14,970
in recent years,

78
00:03:14,970 --> 00:03:15,810
the number of Tibetan antelopes

79
00:03:15,810 --> 00:03:16,750
has dropped from 200,000

80
00:03:16,750 --> 00:03:18,090
to 30,000.

81
00:03:18,340 --> 00:03:19,370
At this rate—

82
00:03:19,390 --> 00:03:21,320
What exactly are you trying to say?

83
00:03:24,850 --> 00:03:25,630
I'm saying,

84
00:03:27,750 --> 00:03:28,980
given the Mountain Patrol's current

85
00:03:28,980 --> 00:03:30,840
scale and enforcement strength,

86
00:03:32,890 --> 00:03:33,790
you won't be able to prevent

87
00:03:33,790 --> 00:03:36,120
the Tibetan antelope from going extinct.

88
00:03:42,750 --> 00:03:43,410
I know.

89
00:03:45,970 --> 00:03:46,930
In three years,

90
00:03:48,320 --> 00:03:49,520
or five at the latest,

91
00:03:50,590 --> 00:03:52,210
the Tibetan antelopes in Bolamula

92
00:03:52,210 --> 00:03:53,680
will be completely extinct.

93
00:03:53,680 --> 00:03:54,620
So... that's why

94
00:03:54,650 --> 00:03:56,590
we need to come up with something else.

95
00:03:56,590 --> 00:03:58,000
What else can we do?

96
00:03:59,360 --> 00:04:00,250
Expand the Mountain Patrol.

97
00:04:00,250 --> 00:04:00,910
Impossible.

98
00:04:00,910 --> 00:04:02,110
The county can't even

99
00:04:02,130 --> 00:04:02,700
pay our salaries.

100
00:04:02,700 --> 00:04:03,550
How could they afford to hire more people?

101
00:04:03,550 --> 00:04:04,560
No matter how much

102
00:04:04,590 --> 00:04:05,360
you expand the Mountain Patrol,

103
00:04:05,360 --> 00:04:07,160
it won't solve the root problem.

104
00:04:12,250 --> 00:04:13,780
There is only one solution.

105
00:04:15,670 --> 00:04:17,269
Establish a nature reserve.

106
00:04:18,810 --> 00:04:20,010
A nature reserve?

107
00:04:20,760 --> 00:04:22,440
A reserve for protecting
Tibetan antelopes?

108
00:04:22,440 --> 00:04:22,880
Yes.

109
00:04:23,650 --> 00:04:24,320
Right.

110
00:04:28,790 --> 00:04:30,060
That's the only way.

111
00:04:30,870 --> 00:04:31,670
You know that?

112
00:04:32,650 --> 00:04:34,050
You've thought of it too?

113
00:04:35,430 --> 00:04:36,570
For our task,

114
00:04:37,790 --> 00:04:39,700
a provincial reserve won't suffice.

115
00:04:39,700 --> 00:04:40,920
It must be a national

116
00:04:40,950 --> 00:04:41,890
nature reserve.

117
00:04:43,180 --> 00:04:44,220
Uniting Qinghai,

118
00:04:44,250 --> 00:04:46,100
Tibet, and Xinjiang,

119
00:04:46,630 --> 00:04:47,710
completely sealing off

120
00:04:47,710 --> 00:04:49,310
the entire Bolamula region.

121
00:04:50,630 --> 00:04:51,760
To give the Tibetan antelopes

122
00:04:51,760 --> 00:04:53,350
enough space and time

123
00:04:53,430 --> 00:04:55,090
to recover their population.

124
00:04:57,480 --> 00:04:58,560
A reserve?

125
00:04:58,580 --> 00:05:00,440
What about the development zone?

126
00:05:09,770 --> 00:05:10,390
Mr. Shao,

127
00:05:11,600 --> 00:05:13,730
could you please step out for a moment?

128
00:05:14,010 --> 00:05:14,400
Sure.

129
00:05:31,810 --> 00:05:32,400
Captain,

130
00:05:34,110 --> 00:05:36,040
the Economic Development Zone...

131
00:05:36,159 --> 00:05:37,360
are we still doing it?

132
00:05:42,830 --> 00:05:44,760
Establishing a nature reserve...

133
00:05:45,030 --> 00:05:46,440
is just my personal idea.

134
00:05:48,330 --> 00:05:50,130
It hasn't fully taken shape yet.

135
00:05:52,810 --> 00:05:53,330
So I didn't

136
00:05:53,330 --> 00:05:54,340
tell you guys.

137
00:05:56,540 --> 00:05:58,800
Will the county authorities approve it?

138
00:05:58,800 --> 00:05:59,540
I don't know.

139
00:06:00,770 --> 00:06:02,630
I haven't reported it to them yet.

140
00:06:03,580 --> 00:06:05,780
Will we still get permanent positions?

141
00:06:14,900 --> 00:06:16,230
I know you're all hoping

142
00:06:16,810 --> 00:06:17,710
for the development zone

143
00:06:17,710 --> 00:06:19,040
to be established soon,

144
00:06:20,530 --> 00:06:22,130
so your lives can stabilize.

145
00:06:24,520 --> 00:06:25,130
But you heard it

146
00:06:25,130 --> 00:06:26,190
just now.

147
00:06:27,440 --> 00:06:29,170
Establishing a nature reserve

148
00:06:29,950 --> 00:06:30,920
is the only way to restore Bolamula

149
00:06:30,920 --> 00:06:32,600
to its original state.

150
00:06:36,190 --> 00:06:38,250
This path will definitely be harder.

151
00:06:43,600 --> 00:06:44,320
We won't get to be managers

152
00:06:44,320 --> 00:06:45,920
or deputy managers anymore.

153
00:06:47,030 --> 00:06:50,159
And permanent positions might not
happen anytime soon.

154
00:06:54,860 --> 00:06:56,659
You might want to think about...

155
00:06:57,920 --> 00:06:59,320
if you want to keep going.

156
00:06:59,790 --> 00:07:01,390
What is there to think about?

157
00:07:02,680 --> 00:07:03,940
I'll follow your lead.

158
00:07:06,060 --> 00:07:06,830
Whatever you tell me to do,

159
00:07:06,830 --> 00:07:07,450
I'll do it.

160
00:07:09,830 --> 00:07:11,760
I don't need a permanent position.

161
00:07:14,380 --> 00:07:16,240
When the reserve is established,

162
00:07:16,340 --> 00:07:17,960
can I still go on patrol?

163
00:07:19,960 --> 00:07:20,960
I promise you can.

164
00:07:22,650 --> 00:07:23,270
Okay.

165
00:07:24,480 --> 00:07:25,680
I'm a police officer.

166
00:07:26,430 --> 00:07:27,260
I don't care about

167
00:07:27,260 --> 00:07:28,320
the manager thing.

168
00:07:29,850 --> 00:07:31,310
Many people don't realize

169
00:07:31,770 --> 00:07:33,070
how important it is to protect

170
00:07:33,070 --> 00:07:34,200
Tibetan antelopes.

171
00:07:35,409 --> 00:07:35,950
Only we

172
00:07:35,980 --> 00:07:37,440
can make them understand.

173
00:07:38,740 --> 00:07:40,190
We forge our own paths.

174
00:07:40,920 --> 00:07:42,120
There's always a way.

175
00:07:43,080 --> 00:07:43,640
Yes.

176
00:07:45,630 --> 00:07:46,250
I...

177
00:07:47,050 --> 00:07:48,310
I've walked away once.

178
00:07:48,620 --> 00:07:50,480
I'd be too ashamed to leave again.

179
00:08:33,090 --> 00:08:34,179
Leave at dawn.

180
00:08:35,309 --> 00:08:36,570
It's not safe at night.

181
00:08:39,960 --> 00:08:40,490
Captain,

182
00:08:41,960 --> 00:08:44,420
have you ever considered us
your own people?

183
00:08:47,860 --> 00:08:49,690
You've been with me the longest.

184
00:08:50,950 --> 00:08:52,370
You shouldn't be asking that.

185
00:08:52,370 --> 00:08:52,960
Yes.

186
00:08:53,890 --> 00:08:55,690
I have been with you the longest.

187
00:08:55,940 --> 00:08:57,600
That's why I don't understand

188
00:08:57,670 --> 00:08:58,930
why you're keep it from us

189
00:08:58,930 --> 00:09:00,550
and making this decision on your own.

190
00:09:00,550 --> 00:09:01,480
If Mr. Shao hadn't

191
00:09:01,480 --> 00:09:02,850
talked to you about this today

192
00:09:02,850 --> 00:09:03,980
with all of us there,

193
00:09:04,390 --> 00:09:06,590
you would've gone on keeping it from us.

194
00:09:07,250 --> 00:09:08,850
Whenever someone complains

195
00:09:08,850 --> 00:09:10,270
or feels like giving up,

196
00:09:10,460 --> 00:09:11,550
I always tell them,

197
00:09:12,220 --> 00:09:14,180
"things will get better once the
development zone is set up."

198
00:09:14,180 --> 00:09:14,850
It's almost

199
00:09:14,870 --> 00:09:16,190
become my mantra.

200
00:09:16,910 --> 00:09:17,550
You gave me

201
00:09:17,570 --> 00:09:18,830
a warm jar to hold onto.

202
00:09:19,150 --> 00:09:19,890
And I gave them

203
00:09:19,890 --> 00:09:21,420
each a warm jar to hold onto.

204
00:09:21,740 --> 00:09:22,430
Now you're going to

205
00:09:22,430 --> 00:09:23,630
get us all laid off by the county,

206
00:09:23,630 --> 00:09:24,920
and take the warm jars in everyone's hands

207
00:09:24,920 --> 00:09:25,940
and smash them.

208
00:09:29,120 --> 00:09:29,830
Is this how

209
00:09:29,860 --> 00:09:31,320
you treat your own people?

210
00:09:33,620 --> 00:09:34,320
Captain,

211
00:09:35,360 --> 00:09:35,990
you're not

212
00:09:36,010 --> 00:09:37,940
the only member of the patrol team.

213
00:09:38,080 --> 00:09:38,790
It takes

214
00:09:38,820 --> 00:09:40,100
all of us

215
00:09:40,630 --> 00:09:41,820
to be a team.

216
00:09:52,910 --> 00:09:53,590
I know

217
00:09:53,610 --> 00:09:54,750
the tax office is directly administered,

218
00:09:54,750 --> 00:09:56,210
not managed by the county.

219
00:09:56,840 --> 00:09:58,000
If you won't speak up for the county,

220
00:09:58,000 --> 00:09:58,520
that's fine,

221
00:09:58,520 --> 00:10:00,360
but you shouldn't add fuel to the fire.

222
00:10:00,360 --> 00:10:01,410
The state of the county's finances...

223
00:10:01,410 --> 00:10:03,070
Don't act like you don't know.

224
00:10:04,510 --> 00:10:05,320
Mayor Lin,

225
00:10:05,620 --> 00:10:07,020
we're in a tough spot too.

226
00:10:07,800 --> 00:10:09,530
Things are hard for the county.

227
00:10:09,820 --> 00:10:10,720
We know that.

228
00:10:11,030 --> 00:10:12,040
We're stuck in the middle.

229
00:10:12,040 --> 00:10:13,770
We're the bad guys to everyone.

230
00:10:13,790 --> 00:10:15,100
We can't do our job.

231
00:10:16,270 --> 00:10:17,860
Tell me, what should we do?

232
00:10:17,920 --> 00:10:19,400
Anyway, we can't pay the tax right now.

233
00:10:19,400 --> 00:10:20,530
You'll have to wait.

234
00:10:20,840 --> 00:10:22,460
We've been waiting forever.

235
00:10:23,010 --> 00:10:25,210
Please try to understand our position.

236
00:10:25,700 --> 00:10:26,370
How about

237
00:10:26,770 --> 00:10:28,170
we discuss this further?

238
00:10:34,700 --> 00:10:35,100
Here.

239
00:10:36,200 --> 00:10:37,260
Look for yourself.

240
00:10:37,410 --> 00:10:39,050
Last year, Gela Township sold

241
00:10:39,050 --> 00:10:40,500
16,000 cattle and sheep.

242
00:10:40,840 --> 00:10:41,580
This year?

243
00:10:41,600 --> 00:10:43,100
Less than 2,000!

244
00:10:43,230 --> 00:10:44,770
Is it because the herdsmen
don't want to sell?

245
00:10:44,770 --> 00:10:47,080
It's because they were lost
in the snow disaster!

246
00:10:47,080 --> 00:10:47,780
You think cattle and sheep

247
00:10:47,780 --> 00:10:49,050
are like snow on the mountains,

248
00:10:49,050 --> 00:10:50,860
melting and flowing down in the sun?

249
00:10:50,860 --> 00:10:51,920
You want me to bring

250
00:10:51,940 --> 00:10:52,820
local officials

251
00:10:52,820 --> 00:10:53,700
to the herdsmen's homes

252
00:10:53,700 --> 00:10:54,670
and take away the cattle and sheep

253
00:10:54,670 --> 00:10:55,910
they're keeping for the winter?

254
00:10:55,910 --> 00:10:56,770
I'm asking you!

255
00:11:00,960 --> 00:11:01,670
Mayor Lin,

256
00:11:02,630 --> 00:11:03,270
I'll be going then.

257
00:11:03,270 --> 00:11:05,670
You shouldn't have come
in the first place.

258
00:11:14,620 --> 00:11:16,290
What now? Come in.

259
00:11:20,860 --> 00:11:21,510
Mayor Lin.

260
00:11:22,510 --> 00:11:23,220
He?

261
00:11:24,560 --> 00:11:25,230
What is it?

262
00:11:40,530 --> 00:11:41,550
A reserve?

263
00:11:42,480 --> 00:11:43,310
Where did this

264
00:11:43,340 --> 00:11:44,400
reserve come from?

265
00:11:44,510 --> 00:11:46,110
Where are you talking about?

266
00:11:47,030 --> 00:11:48,830
It's a national nature reserve.

267
00:11:49,840 --> 00:11:50,630
The Tibetan antelope population

268
00:11:50,630 --> 00:11:52,100
is on the brink of extinction.

269
00:11:52,100 --> 00:11:52,650
The idea of

270
00:11:52,650 --> 00:11:53,950
developing first and cleaning up later

271
00:11:53,950 --> 00:11:55,950
is no longer suitable for Bolamula.

272
00:11:56,790 --> 00:11:58,200
So we must apply for

273
00:11:58,230 --> 00:11:59,520
state intervention.

274
00:11:59,670 --> 00:12:00,570
Where were you before?

275
00:12:00,570 --> 00:12:01,770
Why bring this up now?

276
00:12:04,040 --> 00:12:05,720
The idea of establishing a reserve

277
00:12:05,720 --> 00:12:07,380
is something I've always had.

278
00:12:07,540 --> 00:12:08,370
But I delayed

279
00:12:08,440 --> 00:12:10,630
reporting it to the County
Party Committee,

280
00:12:10,630 --> 00:12:11,500
and I didn't even tell

281
00:12:11,500 --> 00:12:13,230
anyone in the Mountain Patrol.

282
00:12:14,550 --> 00:12:15,150
Simply because

283
00:12:15,150 --> 00:12:15,600
this in itself

284
00:12:15,600 --> 00:12:16,930
is a contradiction.

285
00:12:18,000 --> 00:12:18,520
With just

286
00:12:18,520 --> 00:12:19,920
our county's resources,

287
00:12:20,610 --> 00:12:22,010
we can't find a solution.

288
00:12:23,120 --> 00:12:24,290
As a Party member,

289
00:12:25,360 --> 00:12:26,120
I can complete

290
00:12:26,120 --> 00:12:28,130
the tasks assigned to me
by the organization

291
00:12:28,130 --> 00:12:29,930
and set up the development zone.

292
00:12:30,860 --> 00:12:32,400
But as a Mazhi native,

293
00:12:32,750 --> 00:12:34,050
I cannot watch the environment

294
00:12:34,050 --> 00:12:35,380
be destroyed at my hands.

295
00:12:35,380 --> 00:12:36,310
Comrade Duojie,

296
00:12:37,050 --> 00:12:38,220
mind your words.

297
00:12:38,860 --> 00:12:40,170
Are you trying to pit our Party

298
00:12:40,170 --> 00:12:41,940
against environmental issues?

299
00:12:41,940 --> 00:12:43,400
Both Secretary Chen and I

300
00:12:43,460 --> 00:12:45,190
have emphasized more than once

301
00:12:45,200 --> 00:12:46,450
that our future development

302
00:12:46,450 --> 00:12:47,510
must be scientific

303
00:12:47,590 --> 00:12:48,650
and standardized.

304
00:12:48,690 --> 00:12:50,390
It's not about reckless exploitation.

305
00:12:50,390 --> 00:12:51,190
Furthermore,

306
00:12:51,390 --> 00:12:53,450
we are only in the exploration phase.

307
00:12:53,500 --> 00:12:54,390
Investment promotion hasn't even

308
00:12:54,390 --> 00:12:55,220
officially started yet.

309
00:12:55,220 --> 00:12:56,350
What makes you think

310
00:12:56,360 --> 00:12:57,050
that development must be

311
00:12:57,050 --> 00:12:57,840
destructive?

312
00:12:57,840 --> 00:12:58,390
On what grounds?

313
00:12:58,390 --> 00:12:59,080
Mayor Lin,

314
00:12:59,480 --> 00:13:00,220
what I just said

315
00:13:00,220 --> 00:13:01,390
wasn't said lightly.

316
00:13:01,390 --> 00:13:01,890
I have conducted

317
00:13:01,890 --> 00:13:03,020
thorough research.

318
00:13:04,390 --> 00:13:05,150
Yecuo Lake Wetland—

319
00:13:05,150 --> 00:13:06,200
have you heard of it?

320
00:13:06,200 --> 00:13:06,750
It is less than

321
00:13:06,750 --> 00:13:08,000
700 kilometers from here.

322
00:13:08,000 --> 00:13:08,600
Three years ago,

323
00:13:08,600 --> 00:13:09,100
it was still

324
00:13:09,100 --> 00:13:09,910
a lush wetland.

325
00:13:09,910 --> 00:13:10,770
But now?

326
00:13:10,980 --> 00:13:11,940
Because of mining,

327
00:13:11,940 --> 00:13:13,000
water got polluted,

328
00:13:13,000 --> 00:13:13,980
groundwater was drained,

329
00:13:13,980 --> 00:13:15,200
creating hollows,

330
00:13:15,300 --> 00:13:17,000
and grasslands have turned into desert.

331
00:13:17,000 --> 00:13:17,960
The herdsmen's pastures

332
00:13:17,960 --> 00:13:19,360
have all been destroyed.

333
00:13:19,480 --> 00:13:20,280
Let me ask you.

334
00:13:20,520 --> 00:13:22,120
When these mining companies

335
00:13:22,220 --> 00:13:22,750
finish stripping the mine

336
00:13:22,750 --> 00:13:23,840
and leave,

337
00:13:23,860 --> 00:13:25,480
what's left, will it still be wetlands?

338
00:13:25,480 --> 00:13:26,880
It'll just be a dead zone!

339
00:13:37,870 --> 00:13:38,730
Mr. Secretary,

340
00:13:40,830 --> 00:13:43,760
this is an environmental
assessment report I wrote.

341
00:13:44,050 --> 00:13:44,860
Bolamula

342
00:13:44,890 --> 00:13:46,620
is in the Sanjiangyuan region.

343
00:13:47,100 --> 00:13:48,160
Glacial meltwater

344
00:13:48,360 --> 00:13:50,220
flows into many rivers.

345
00:13:50,690 --> 00:13:52,380
If we mine here,

346
00:13:52,840 --> 00:13:53,880
and it affects

347
00:13:53,910 --> 00:13:55,130
the midstream and downstream

348
00:13:55,130 --> 00:13:56,530
water quality and volume,

349
00:13:56,530 --> 00:13:57,260
we become

350
00:13:57,290 --> 00:13:58,400
criminals against the country

351
00:13:58,400 --> 00:13:59,500
and humanity.

352
00:14:07,200 --> 00:14:08,850
The importance of economic development,

353
00:14:08,850 --> 00:14:10,250
I've mentioned it

354
00:14:10,280 --> 00:14:11,680
at least a hundred times.

355
00:14:12,770 --> 00:14:13,440
Right now,

356
00:14:13,850 --> 00:14:15,320
there are entrepreneurs

357
00:14:15,790 --> 00:14:17,080
with money in hand

358
00:14:17,160 --> 00:14:19,170
waiting to invest in Mazhi County

359
00:14:19,200 --> 00:14:20,710
and Bolamula.

360
00:14:20,910 --> 00:14:22,370
What are they waiting for?

361
00:14:22,770 --> 00:14:23,700
Comrade Duojie,

362
00:14:23,880 --> 00:14:24,720
they are waiting for

363
00:14:24,720 --> 00:14:26,180
your exploration report.

364
00:14:27,860 --> 00:14:29,220
This is not negotiable.

365
00:14:29,580 --> 00:14:30,270
It cannot be changed

366
00:14:30,270 --> 00:14:31,420
by anyone's

367
00:14:31,450 --> 00:14:32,310
personal will.

368
00:14:35,270 --> 00:14:37,000
Developing mineral resources

369
00:14:37,050 --> 00:14:38,430
is the fastest way

370
00:14:38,620 --> 00:14:39,960
to increase tax revenue

371
00:14:39,980 --> 00:14:41,200
and modernize Mazhi.

372
00:14:42,290 --> 00:14:42,800
But if

373
00:14:42,820 --> 00:14:44,880
destroying the natural environment

374
00:14:45,170 --> 00:14:46,630
and causing irreversible damage

375
00:14:46,630 --> 00:14:48,440
to animal and plant resources

376
00:14:48,460 --> 00:14:49,200
is the price,

377
00:14:50,950 --> 00:14:52,310
then as a Party member,

378
00:14:54,040 --> 00:14:55,040
a native of Mazhi,

379
00:14:56,190 --> 00:14:57,450
and a child of herdsmen

380
00:14:57,450 --> 00:14:59,160
who grew up here,

381
00:15:01,610 --> 00:15:02,440
this is not

382
00:15:02,460 --> 00:15:03,920
the modernization I want.

383
00:15:04,560 --> 00:15:06,030
Such modernization

384
00:15:06,270 --> 00:15:07,070
also goes against

385
00:15:07,070 --> 00:15:08,330
our Party's policy.

386
00:15:08,670 --> 00:15:09,440
There is no point

387
00:15:09,440 --> 00:15:10,640
in arguing like this.

388
00:15:10,860 --> 00:15:11,670
We cannot

389
00:15:11,700 --> 00:15:12,620
set up an economic

390
00:15:12,620 --> 00:15:13,820
development zone first

391
00:15:13,820 --> 00:15:14,670
to see if

392
00:15:14,690 --> 00:15:16,210
it destroys the environment.

393
00:15:16,210 --> 00:15:16,700
Or

394
00:15:16,770 --> 00:15:18,480
establish a nature reserve

395
00:15:18,600 --> 00:15:19,370
and then think about

396
00:15:19,370 --> 00:15:20,900
how to develop the economy.

397
00:15:21,480 --> 00:15:22,150
What do the Party

398
00:15:22,150 --> 00:15:23,080
and the people

399
00:15:23,100 --> 00:15:24,060
expect us to do here?

400
00:15:24,060 --> 00:15:25,640
To get things done,

401
00:15:25,670 --> 00:15:26,510
comrades.

402
00:15:28,050 --> 00:15:29,780
As for the exploration report,

403
00:15:30,790 --> 00:15:31,360
Comrade Duojie

404
00:15:31,360 --> 00:15:32,240
still needs to submit it

405
00:15:32,240 --> 00:15:33,090
to the county.

406
00:15:34,530 --> 00:15:36,460
If he insists on not submitting it,

407
00:15:37,750 --> 00:15:38,440
I will bring up

408
00:15:38,440 --> 00:15:40,770
the proposal from the last meeting again—

409
00:15:41,200 --> 00:15:42,800
disband the Mountain Patrol

410
00:15:44,650 --> 00:15:46,910
and re-establish the exploration team.

411
00:15:47,550 --> 00:15:48,220
Hang on.

412
00:15:48,910 --> 00:15:50,030
Let me share my thoughts.

413
00:15:50,030 --> 00:15:50,960
Comrade Duojie,

414
00:15:52,430 --> 00:15:53,760
regarding the reserve,

415
00:15:54,870 --> 00:15:56,800
it's not that we can't consider it,

416
00:15:57,650 --> 00:15:58,390
but

417
00:15:58,500 --> 00:16:00,120
we can't just listen to you

418
00:16:00,820 --> 00:16:01,760
and look at

419
00:16:01,790 --> 00:16:03,320
the pelts you brought back.

420
00:16:03,480 --> 00:16:04,290
You must give me

421
00:16:04,290 --> 00:16:05,200
a formal report

422
00:16:05,270 --> 00:16:06,740
with a feasible plan.

423
00:16:07,600 --> 00:16:08,300
Otherwise,

424
00:16:08,330 --> 00:16:10,500
the county can't support your proposal

425
00:16:10,500 --> 00:16:12,050
to apply to the superiors.

426
00:16:12,870 --> 00:16:14,070
Okay, Mr. Secretary.

427
00:16:14,860 --> 00:16:15,650
I will submit the formal report

428
00:16:15,650 --> 00:16:16,780
as soon as possible.

429
00:16:20,080 --> 00:16:21,600
But as you know,

430
00:16:22,240 --> 00:16:23,080
the subsidies

431
00:16:23,100 --> 00:16:24,950
need to go to units that need them more.

432
00:16:24,950 --> 00:16:27,410
How the Mountain Patrol will be maintained,

433
00:16:27,990 --> 00:16:28,770
you'll have to figure out

434
00:16:28,770 --> 00:16:29,840
on your own.

435
00:16:34,240 --> 00:16:34,970
Understood.

436
00:16:36,040 --> 00:16:37,700
It's not going to be easy.

437
00:16:38,940 --> 00:16:40,410
The Mountain Patrol's salaries

438
00:16:40,410 --> 00:16:42,170
used to be paid by the county.

439
00:16:43,000 --> 00:16:44,600
Although there were delays,

440
00:16:44,890 --> 00:16:46,420
they were paid eventually.

441
00:16:47,410 --> 00:16:47,760
Now

442
00:16:47,790 --> 00:16:49,520
you'll be entirely on your own.

443
00:16:50,390 --> 00:16:52,050
You might want to reconsider.

444
00:16:56,700 --> 00:16:58,160
It's okay, Mr. Secretary.

445
00:16:58,710 --> 00:17:00,260
I'm very grateful that

446
00:17:00,410 --> 00:17:02,210
Mazhi has supported us until now

447
00:17:02,390 --> 00:17:04,720
despite being a poverty-stricken county.

448
00:17:04,720 --> 00:17:05,720
I believe

449
00:17:05,810 --> 00:17:06,790
the Mountain Patrol members

450
00:17:06,790 --> 00:17:07,990
will understand too.

451
00:17:43,980 --> 00:17:44,780
The year before last, I established

452
00:17:44,780 --> 00:17:47,110
the Mazhi Economic Development Company.

453
00:17:49,420 --> 00:17:51,420
I posted notices around the county.

454
00:17:54,390 --> 00:17:54,830
I remember

455
00:17:54,830 --> 00:17:56,290
you were the first to come.

456
00:17:59,600 --> 00:18:01,060
At that time, I thought,

457
00:18:02,070 --> 00:18:02,940
I was in luck.

458
00:18:05,350 --> 00:18:06,810
This company will make it.

459
00:18:08,870 --> 00:18:10,200
The first person to come

460
00:18:10,830 --> 00:18:11,260
was such

461
00:18:11,260 --> 00:18:12,480
a fine young man.

462
00:18:14,200 --> 00:18:15,530
A high school graduate.

463
00:18:18,960 --> 00:18:20,090
My company's future

464
00:18:21,610 --> 00:18:23,610
will definitely be extraordinary.

465
00:18:28,440 --> 00:18:29,970
But who would have thought,

466
00:18:31,910 --> 00:18:33,310
for those who came later,

467
00:18:34,310 --> 00:18:35,000
having attended primary school

468
00:18:35,000 --> 00:18:36,860
was considered highly educated.

469
00:18:38,830 --> 00:18:40,500
So I relied on you heavily.

470
00:18:41,700 --> 00:18:43,030
I made you Vice Captain.

471
00:18:43,660 --> 00:18:46,090
Sent you to learn geological surveying.

472
00:18:46,860 --> 00:18:48,390
Managing money and people.

473
00:18:50,530 --> 00:18:51,570
I thought that one day,

474
00:18:51,570 --> 00:18:52,970
when I can no longer work,

475
00:18:53,770 --> 00:18:55,100
you could take my place.

476
00:19:03,770 --> 00:19:05,110
This was my mistake.

477
00:19:10,940 --> 00:19:12,120
You put so much effort

478
00:19:12,120 --> 00:19:14,120
into the mineral exploration work.

479
00:19:16,480 --> 00:19:17,740
Now I've stopped it,

480
00:19:18,630 --> 00:19:19,830
and I kept it from you.

481
00:19:21,710 --> 00:19:22,770
I've let you down.

482
00:19:25,180 --> 00:19:27,110
I'll discuss with County Mayor Lin

483
00:19:27,480 --> 00:19:28,290
and find a suitable position

484
00:19:28,290 --> 00:19:29,270
for you.

485
00:19:31,270 --> 00:19:33,530
You have a good educational background.

486
00:19:33,680 --> 00:19:34,610
Getting a permanent position

487
00:19:34,610 --> 00:19:35,670
shouldn't be hard.

488
00:19:56,110 --> 00:19:56,850
He.

489
00:19:59,010 --> 00:20:00,340
I also want to thank you.

490
00:20:02,350 --> 00:20:03,210
Because of you,

491
00:20:03,350 --> 00:20:04,590
I made up my mind earlier

492
00:20:04,590 --> 00:20:05,960
to set up the reserve.

493
00:20:08,100 --> 00:20:09,300
If it weren't for you,

494
00:20:10,510 --> 00:20:11,160
I don't know

495
00:20:11,160 --> 00:20:12,740
how long I would have dragged my feet

496
00:20:12,740 --> 00:20:14,870
before bringing it up with the county.

497
00:20:32,570 --> 00:20:33,280
♪ My dear friends ♪

498
00:20:33,280 --> 00:20:36,810
[Protect Bolamula Together]

499
00:20:36,810 --> 00:20:37,400
Protecting Tibetan antelopes

500
00:20:37,400 --> 00:20:37,700
♪ From around the world ♪

501
00:20:37,700 --> 00:20:39,180
is everyone's responsibility.

502
00:20:39,180 --> 00:20:39,580
Hello.

503
00:20:39,680 --> 00:20:40,460
Protecting Tibetan antelopes

504
00:20:40,460 --> 00:20:41,250
is everyone's responsibility.

505
00:20:41,250 --> 00:20:43,850
Please help us spread the word
when you go back.

506
00:20:45,330 --> 00:20:49,860
♪ We meet on this auspicious day ♪

507
00:20:49,950 --> 00:20:53,010
♪ Let's raise our glasses and sing ♪

508
00:20:53,010 --> 00:20:53,880
The mirror reflection on your face.
So pretty.

509
00:20:53,880 --> 00:20:55,330
♪ Please have this drink ♪

510
00:20:55,330 --> 00:20:55,810
Dad!

511
00:20:56,750 --> 00:20:57,810
That's good. Okay.

512
00:20:58,550 --> 00:20:59,350
Next one.

513
00:20:59,770 --> 00:21:00,220
Hurry.

514
00:21:00,250 --> 00:21:00,920
Come on.

515
00:21:01,740 --> 00:21:02,420
Sit down.

516
00:21:03,070 --> 00:21:03,830
Okay.

517
00:21:07,050 --> 00:21:08,510
Good. Very good.

518
00:21:08,610 --> 00:21:09,220
Smile.

519
00:21:09,690 --> 00:21:10,320
Nice.

520
00:21:10,380 --> 00:21:11,240
♪ My dear friends ♪

521
00:21:11,240 --> 00:21:11,980
Okay. It's fine.

522
00:21:11,980 --> 00:21:13,380
Tilt your head like this.

523
00:21:14,010 --> 00:21:14,920
Okay. Perfect.

524
00:21:15,200 --> 00:21:15,540
Next.

525
00:21:15,540 --> 00:21:16,720
♪ There are three toasts to be made ♪

526
00:21:16,720 --> 00:21:17,500
A little closer.

527
00:21:17,500 --> 00:21:18,180
Thank you.

528
00:21:20,420 --> 00:21:22,290
♪ To the Three Supreme Gods ♪

529
00:21:22,290 --> 00:21:23,530
Let me change the film.

530
00:21:23,530 --> 00:21:24,730
Please wait a moment.

531
00:21:25,110 --> 00:21:25,460
Here.

532
00:21:28,120 --> 00:21:30,480
♪ To our parents ♪

533
00:21:30,480 --> 00:21:31,030
Are we turning this place

534
00:21:31,030 --> 00:21:32,160
into a photo studio?

535
00:21:32,200 --> 00:21:33,020
♪ To our relatives and friends ♪

536
00:21:33,020 --> 00:21:34,880
That doesn't seem like a bad idea.

537
00:21:37,360 --> 00:21:37,540
♪ My dear friends ♪

538
00:21:37,540 --> 00:21:42,680
[Those who hunt Tibetan antelopes must die.]

539
00:21:42,680 --> 00:21:50,270
♪ A toast for blessings ♪

540
00:21:50,610 --> 00:21:55,080
♪ Wishing you good luck and health ♪

541
00:21:55,190 --> 00:21:58,920
♪ Wishing for blessings as vast
as the East Sea ♪

542
00:21:59,320 --> 00:22:02,350
♪ Blessing all of you ♪

543
00:22:02,350 --> 00:22:04,990
[Tibetan antelopes need our protection.]

544
00:22:05,070 --> 00:22:09,260
[Hunting Tibetan antelopes is a criminal offense.]

545
00:22:10,840 --> 00:22:11,730
Okay, done.

546
00:22:14,200 --> 00:22:14,860
Out of film.

547
00:22:15,420 --> 00:22:16,080
Out of film?

548
00:22:16,680 --> 00:22:17,200
Let me change it.

549
00:22:17,200 --> 00:22:18,160
Changing the film.

550
00:22:18,160 --> 00:22:19,360
Please wait a moment.

551
00:22:19,620 --> 00:22:20,990
Abuse of power.

552
00:22:21,160 --> 00:22:23,620
Using the office camera
to make extra money.

553
00:22:25,150 --> 00:22:26,260
Heaven knows,

554
00:22:26,770 --> 00:22:27,700
not a single penny

555
00:22:27,700 --> 00:22:28,850
went into my pocket.

556
00:22:29,050 --> 00:22:30,180
I handed it all over.

557
00:22:30,540 --> 00:22:31,760
You eat our food,

558
00:22:31,920 --> 00:22:32,880
live in our place.

559
00:22:32,880 --> 00:22:34,350
Paying is only right.

560
00:22:34,680 --> 00:22:36,210
I contributed the film, didn't I?

561
00:22:36,210 --> 00:22:37,650
The camera belongs to
the newspaper office,

562
00:22:37,650 --> 00:22:39,130
the venue is ours.

563
00:22:39,290 --> 00:22:40,150
Only that cheap film

564
00:22:40,150 --> 00:22:40,780
is yours.

565
00:22:41,310 --> 00:22:42,510
And you feel wronged?

566
00:22:44,450 --> 00:22:46,180
You sure know how to do the math.

567
00:22:46,460 --> 00:22:46,980
Accountant Bai,

568
00:22:46,980 --> 00:22:48,590
do you want to take a photo?

569
00:22:48,900 --> 00:22:50,330
I don't like taking photos.

570
00:22:50,330 --> 00:22:50,880
What girl

571
00:22:50,900 --> 00:22:52,500
doesn't like taking photos?

572
00:22:52,610 --> 00:22:54,180
I think I'm ugly.

573
00:22:54,460 --> 00:22:55,310
Alright?

574
00:22:57,050 --> 00:22:58,030
Really?

575
00:22:58,140 --> 00:22:59,170
Okay, impressive.

576
00:22:59,170 --> 00:23:00,500
Harsh even to yourself.

577
00:23:03,380 --> 00:23:03,950
Captain.

578
00:23:04,230 --> 00:23:04,820
Vice Captain.

579
00:23:04,820 --> 00:23:06,550
You two should take a photo together.

580
00:23:06,550 --> 00:23:08,220
Come on, take a photo together.

581
00:23:08,220 --> 00:23:08,810
Come on.

582
00:23:08,830 --> 00:23:09,220
Take one.

583
00:23:09,220 --> 00:23:10,110
Come on.

584
00:23:10,140 --> 00:23:10,600
Come on.

585
00:23:10,770 --> 00:23:11,160
Take one.

586
00:23:11,160 --> 00:23:11,960
Come on.

587
00:23:11,980 --> 00:23:12,810
Come on, take a photo.

588
00:23:12,810 --> 00:23:13,140
Fine.

589
00:23:16,320 --> 00:23:17,580
Sorry to cut in line.

590
00:23:26,250 --> 00:23:28,180
Please move a bit closer together.

591
00:23:31,180 --> 00:23:31,620
Well,

592
00:23:31,690 --> 00:23:32,530
I meant,

593
00:23:32,630 --> 00:23:34,260
do you want to pose like this?

594
00:23:37,140 --> 00:23:37,880
That's it.

595
00:23:37,950 --> 00:23:38,800
Nice. Very nice.

596
00:23:38,800 --> 00:23:39,950
Come on, look this way.

597
00:23:39,950 --> 00:23:40,690
Hold it.

598
00:23:40,940 --> 00:23:43,080
One, two, three.

599
00:23:43,420 --> 00:23:44,420
Done. Perfect.

600
00:23:44,850 --> 00:23:45,460
Come on.

601
00:23:45,490 --> 00:23:46,450
Make way.

602
00:23:47,170 --> 00:23:47,630
Friend.

603
00:23:47,900 --> 00:23:48,470
If you want a photo,

604
00:23:48,470 --> 00:23:49,100
line up over here.

605
00:23:49,100 --> 00:23:50,430
I'm not here for a photo.

606
00:23:52,280 --> 00:23:53,400
Deputy County Mayor Duo.

607
00:23:53,400 --> 00:23:54,430
What brings you here?

608
00:23:54,430 --> 00:23:55,190
I am now

609
00:23:55,220 --> 00:23:56,270
Captain of the Bolamula

610
00:23:56,270 --> 00:23:57,330
Exploration Team.

611
00:23:57,860 --> 00:23:58,750
County Mayor Lin

612
00:23:58,750 --> 00:23:59,610
asked me to come

613
00:23:59,610 --> 00:24:00,740
and say hello to you.

614
00:24:00,850 --> 00:24:01,570
You were doing well

615
00:24:01,570 --> 00:24:03,140
at the animal husbandry station.

616
00:24:03,140 --> 00:24:03,640
How did you

617
00:24:03,640 --> 00:24:04,840
get involved in this?

618
00:24:05,510 --> 00:24:06,610
Well, I too

619
00:24:06,630 --> 00:24:07,850
wanted to contribute

620
00:24:07,880 --> 00:24:09,540
to the county's development.

621
00:24:11,030 --> 00:24:11,680
Go ahead.

622
00:24:12,880 --> 00:24:14,210
What do you want from me?

623
00:24:14,480 --> 00:24:15,220
Mayor Duo,

624
00:24:16,230 --> 00:24:17,510
that place, Bolamula,

625
00:24:17,540 --> 00:24:19,110
I went there once when I was a kid.

626
00:24:19,110 --> 00:24:20,910
I haven't dared to go back since.

627
00:24:21,520 --> 00:24:22,540
To be honest,

628
00:24:23,220 --> 00:24:24,270
about entering the mountains,

629
00:24:24,270 --> 00:24:25,870
I really have no confidence.

630
00:24:26,150 --> 00:24:27,880
So I came to ask for your advice.

631
00:24:28,920 --> 00:24:30,780
It's right to have no confidence.

632
00:24:31,090 --> 00:24:32,690
It's right to be afraid, too.

633
00:24:33,440 --> 00:24:34,000
Bolamula

634
00:24:34,030 --> 00:24:34,900
is not a place where

635
00:24:34,900 --> 00:24:36,160
just anyone can enter.

636
00:24:38,440 --> 00:24:39,220
Even if

637
00:24:39,240 --> 00:24:40,750
you think you are prepared,

638
00:24:40,750 --> 00:24:41,850
once you go in,

639
00:24:41,960 --> 00:24:42,510
you will still encounter

640
00:24:42,510 --> 00:24:44,040
unexpected difficulties.

641
00:24:44,880 --> 00:24:45,570
Exactly.

642
00:24:46,310 --> 00:24:47,870
That's why I came to you.

643
00:24:48,740 --> 00:24:49,610
I heard

644
00:24:49,790 --> 00:24:51,610
you've been into the mountains
a lot this year,

645
00:24:51,610 --> 00:24:52,890
and took a lot of notes.

646
00:24:54,040 --> 00:24:54,910
Your experience

647
00:24:54,910 --> 00:24:56,510
is summarized very clearly.

648
00:24:57,330 --> 00:24:58,990
Right now, supplies and money

649
00:24:59,020 --> 00:24:59,950
don't mean much.

650
00:25:00,590 --> 00:25:01,720
Your mineral exploration notes

651
00:25:01,720 --> 00:25:02,450
are the best.

652
00:25:02,840 --> 00:25:04,140
Please let me take a look.

653
00:25:04,140 --> 00:25:05,940
It'll give me some peace of mind.

654
00:25:08,460 --> 00:25:09,900
I can't give you the notes.

655
00:25:09,900 --> 00:25:10,500
Why?

656
00:25:10,830 --> 00:25:12,630
I'm working for the county, too.

657
00:25:13,000 --> 00:25:13,770
If these notes

658
00:25:13,770 --> 00:25:14,250
fall into

659
00:25:14,250 --> 00:25:15,440
the wrong hands,

660
00:25:16,180 --> 00:25:17,240
it won't help them.

661
00:25:17,590 --> 00:25:18,520
It'll harm them.

662
00:25:18,750 --> 00:25:19,940
Harm them how?

663
00:25:20,420 --> 00:25:22,420
Are you worried I won't do a good job?

664
00:25:22,500 --> 00:25:24,430
Worried you might not do a good job,

665
00:25:24,480 --> 00:25:26,830
but even more worried that
you won't come back.

666
00:25:26,830 --> 00:25:27,400
One of

667
00:25:27,420 --> 00:25:28,570
our team members

668
00:25:29,220 --> 00:25:30,220
died in Bolamula.

669
00:25:30,900 --> 00:25:32,630
Another was injured last year.

670
00:25:32,940 --> 00:25:34,400
There were several others

671
00:25:34,420 --> 00:25:35,510
whose families couldn't take it,

672
00:25:35,510 --> 00:25:37,240
and they couldn't handle it either,

673
00:25:37,240 --> 00:25:38,440
so they all went home.

674
00:25:42,940 --> 00:25:43,940
Come look at this.

675
00:25:50,090 --> 00:25:51,020
This place here.

676
00:25:51,500 --> 00:25:53,420
Last year, a group of placer gold miners

677
00:25:53,420 --> 00:25:54,430
went in with guns.

678
00:25:54,890 --> 00:25:55,870
A few days later,

679
00:25:56,240 --> 00:25:56,940
they started fighting

680
00:25:56,940 --> 00:25:57,870
over territory.

681
00:25:59,720 --> 00:26:00,770
Further north,

682
00:26:01,240 --> 00:26:02,330
there were poachers

683
00:26:02,330 --> 00:26:04,190
who set up camp, posted sentries,

684
00:26:04,270 --> 00:26:05,800
and chased anyone they saw.

685
00:26:06,770 --> 00:26:07,700
We had to drive them out twice

686
00:26:07,700 --> 00:26:08,700
before they left.

687
00:26:09,830 --> 00:26:11,030
So Bolamula

688
00:26:11,550 --> 00:26:12,390
isn't a place you can enter

689
00:26:12,390 --> 00:26:13,920
just because you're brave.

690
00:26:17,570 --> 00:26:19,010
Can we be reasonable?

691
00:26:19,970 --> 00:26:21,510
If that little girl can go
into the mountains,

692
00:26:21,510 --> 00:26:22,950
why can't I?

693
00:26:24,500 --> 00:26:26,310
The fact that my team members can go in

694
00:26:26,310 --> 00:26:27,970
has nothing to do with gender.

695
00:26:28,140 --> 00:26:29,050
It's because she knows

696
00:26:29,050 --> 00:26:29,870
how to survive

697
00:26:29,900 --> 00:26:30,900
in the mountains.

698
00:26:31,510 --> 00:26:33,310
She knows the way, reads the weather,

699
00:26:33,310 --> 00:26:34,530
fixes cars, uses ropes,

700
00:26:34,530 --> 00:26:35,660
and knows first aid.

701
00:26:36,960 --> 00:26:39,140
She relies on skill to
enter the mountains,

702
00:26:39,140 --> 00:26:40,010
not impulse.

703
00:26:43,090 --> 00:26:43,770
Captain.

704
00:26:44,790 --> 00:26:45,330
Come in.

705
00:26:45,640 --> 00:26:46,080
Okay.

706
00:26:48,000 --> 00:26:48,530
Captain.

707
00:26:48,790 --> 00:26:49,790
Your wife is here.

708
00:26:49,790 --> 00:26:51,610
She wants you to go down for a photo.

709
00:26:51,610 --> 00:26:52,050
Okay.

710
00:26:55,500 --> 00:26:56,760
Let's leave it at that.

711
00:26:57,000 --> 00:26:57,480
Send my regards

712
00:26:57,480 --> 00:26:58,770
to County Mayor Lin.

713
00:27:06,940 --> 00:27:07,480
Don't wear this

714
00:27:07,480 --> 00:27:09,500
when you enter the Uninhabited Zone.

715
00:27:09,500 --> 00:27:10,160
Poachers

716
00:27:10,220 --> 00:27:11,750
love this kind of clothing.

717
00:27:30,420 --> 00:27:31,250
These routes

718
00:27:31,330 --> 00:27:32,850
and the distribution of mineral belts

719
00:27:32,850 --> 00:27:34,010
are what the Mountain Patrol

720
00:27:34,010 --> 00:27:35,570
spent a whole year

721
00:27:35,680 --> 00:27:36,770
compiling.

722
00:27:37,310 --> 00:27:38,370
This is a part of it.

723
00:27:38,740 --> 00:27:39,700
Great.

724
00:27:39,770 --> 00:27:41,920
This data is very valuable.

725
00:27:43,920 --> 00:27:44,290
Why did he

726
00:27:44,290 --> 00:27:45,420
only give you these few pages?

727
00:27:45,420 --> 00:27:46,070
Him?

728
00:27:46,690 --> 00:27:48,550
He wouldn't give me a single page.

729
00:27:48,870 --> 00:27:50,530
This all belongs to the state.

730
00:27:50,920 --> 00:27:53,050
I just grabbed a few pages on my way out.

731
00:27:54,420 --> 00:27:56,020
What do you mean, "grabbed"?

732
00:27:56,050 --> 00:27:57,640
You're stealing stuff now?

733
00:28:01,140 --> 00:28:02,070
These documents

734
00:28:02,180 --> 00:28:04,090
were compiled by the Mountain Patrol.

735
00:28:04,090 --> 00:28:04,770
The Mountain Patrol

736
00:28:04,770 --> 00:28:05,980
belongs to the county,

737
00:28:05,980 --> 00:28:07,350
not Duojie.

738
00:28:07,810 --> 00:28:09,540
How can you call this stealing?

739
00:28:09,640 --> 00:28:10,420
I sent you there

740
00:28:10,420 --> 00:28:11,060
not to go

741
00:28:11,090 --> 00:28:12,420
behind his back.

742
00:28:12,500 --> 00:28:14,000
I wanted you to learn from him,

743
00:28:14,000 --> 00:28:14,980
so when you go into the mountains,

744
00:28:14,980 --> 00:28:16,380
it will be helpful to you.

745
00:28:16,500 --> 00:28:17,440
But now you're...

746
00:28:17,440 --> 00:28:19,200
you're escalating the conflict.

747
00:28:19,200 --> 00:28:20,160
Mr. Mayor,

748
00:28:20,680 --> 00:28:21,450
we are now

749
00:28:21,480 --> 00:28:23,530
racing against their nature reserve

750
00:28:23,530 --> 00:28:24,630
to move forward with this

751
00:28:24,630 --> 00:28:25,690
development zone.

752
00:28:26,290 --> 00:28:27,570
Without this data,

753
00:28:27,700 --> 00:28:29,300
how can we catch up with them?

754
00:28:30,110 --> 00:28:30,810
You can...

755
00:28:31,180 --> 00:28:32,050
give me another

756
00:28:32,070 --> 00:28:33,190
year or so,

757
00:28:33,960 --> 00:28:34,760
but the result...

758
00:28:34,760 --> 00:28:35,610
who knows?

759
00:28:39,680 --> 00:28:40,330
Well...

760
00:28:41,550 --> 00:28:43,010
If you can't get over this,

761
00:28:43,350 --> 00:28:44,550
I'll return it to him.

762
00:28:44,790 --> 00:28:45,200
Hey!

763
00:28:51,220 --> 00:28:52,200
Listen,

764
00:28:53,270 --> 00:28:55,870
you have to follow the rules
when doing things.

765
00:28:59,050 --> 00:28:59,790
Things like this

766
00:28:59,790 --> 00:29:01,050
must not happen again.

767
00:29:01,770 --> 00:29:02,570
Okay.

768
00:29:03,550 --> 00:29:04,290
I'm off then.

769
00:29:40,090 --> 00:29:40,820
Take a break.

770
00:29:40,940 --> 00:29:41,400
Have some water.

771
00:29:41,400 --> 00:29:41,850
Okay.

772
00:29:43,050 --> 00:29:43,790
Grandma,

773
00:29:43,820 --> 00:29:44,420
thank you.

774
00:29:52,440 --> 00:29:53,570
Grandma, thank you.

775
00:29:53,860 --> 00:29:56,850
♪ My dear friends ♪

776
00:29:56,850 --> 00:29:57,460
Tired?

777
00:29:59,220 --> 00:29:59,240
♪ From around the world ♪

778
00:29:59,240 --> 00:29:59,900
No.

779
00:30:07,280 --> 00:30:07,370
♪ We meet on this auspicious day ♪

780
00:30:07,370 --> 00:30:09,150
I'm surprised you don't
mind that it's dirty.

781
00:30:09,150 --> 00:30:10,200
Cattle eat grass.

782
00:30:10,350 --> 00:30:11,210
It's not dirty.

783
00:30:11,350 --> 00:30:11,790
I'll put the water here.

784
00:30:11,790 --> 00:30:12,160
♪ Let's raise our glasses and sing ♪

785
00:30:12,160 --> 00:30:12,640
Okay.

786
00:30:15,660 --> 00:30:16,010
I guess you do have some sense.

787
00:30:16,010 --> 00:30:16,550
♪ Please have this drink ♪

788
00:30:16,550 --> 00:30:17,810
You're not too stupid.

789
00:30:19,470 --> 00:30:21,000
Why don't you give it a lick?

790
00:30:22,960 --> 00:30:24,360
I'm not actually stupid.

791
00:30:29,530 --> 00:30:30,270
Wrong spot.

792
00:30:31,420 --> 00:30:31,950
Does it matter?

793
00:30:31,950 --> 00:30:33,050
♪ My dear friends ♪

794
00:30:33,050 --> 00:30:35,050
If the dung is arranged neatly,

795
00:30:35,200 --> 00:30:37,420
it shows the lady of the house is capable.

796
00:30:37,420 --> 00:30:37,460
In our pastoral area,

797
00:30:37,460 --> 00:30:38,440
♪ There are three toasts to be made ♪

798
00:30:38,440 --> 00:30:39,550
we care about this.

799
00:30:39,710 --> 00:30:40,840
Oh really?

800
00:30:42,670 --> 00:30:47,660
♪ To the Three Supreme Gods ♪

801
00:30:47,660 --> 00:30:48,440
Officer Bai.

802
00:30:49,690 --> 00:30:49,870
Can I interview you?

803
00:30:49,870 --> 00:30:53,840
♪ To our parents ♪

804
00:30:53,840 --> 00:30:54,110
About what?

805
00:30:54,110 --> 00:30:55,270
♪ To our relatives and friends ♪

806
00:30:55,270 --> 00:30:56,670
I heard about Dongzhiba.

807
00:30:58,190 --> 00:30:58,630
I think

808
00:30:58,660 --> 00:30:59,420
we could write

809
00:30:59,420 --> 00:31:00,820
a special feature on him.

810
00:31:01,400 --> 00:31:02,370
You are the primary witness

811
00:31:02,370 --> 00:31:03,490
to what happened to Dongzhiba.

812
00:31:03,490 --> 00:31:05,220
I'd like to hear your thoughts.

813
00:31:05,760 --> 00:31:06,960
I have nothing to say.

814
00:31:08,110 --> 00:31:09,530
It's not something to celebrate.

815
00:31:09,530 --> 00:31:10,660
Dongzhiba gave his life

816
00:31:10,660 --> 00:31:11,720
to fight poaching.

817
00:31:11,790 --> 00:31:12,320
This is

818
00:31:12,350 --> 00:31:13,530
a very noble deed.

819
00:31:15,340 --> 00:31:16,030
"Noble"?

820
00:31:17,030 --> 00:31:17,590
Noble.

821
00:31:18,570 --> 00:31:19,700
Not just Dongzhiba.

822
00:31:20,210 --> 00:31:20,700
In my heart,

823
00:31:20,700 --> 00:31:22,100
you are all noble people,

824
00:31:22,250 --> 00:31:24,280
who have risen above base interests.

825
00:31:24,280 --> 00:31:24,680
And

826
00:31:24,700 --> 00:31:25,700
for a great cause,

827
00:31:26,020 --> 00:31:27,000
you sacrifice personal gain,

828
00:31:27,000 --> 00:31:28,130
and even your lives.

829
00:31:29,700 --> 00:31:30,940
This is worth celebrating,

830
00:31:30,940 --> 00:31:32,740
so more people can know about it.

831
00:31:34,740 --> 00:31:36,540
Dongzhiba's father died early.

832
00:31:37,010 --> 00:31:37,810
His mother went away for work

833
00:31:37,810 --> 00:31:39,810
and hasn't been back in three years.

834
00:31:40,110 --> 00:31:41,310
They're illiterate,

835
00:31:42,020 --> 00:31:42,740
so

836
00:31:42,850 --> 00:31:44,310
they never wrote letters.

837
00:31:44,830 --> 00:31:45,680
He and his grandmother

838
00:31:45,680 --> 00:31:47,010
depended on each other.

839
00:31:47,870 --> 00:31:48,220
Officer Bai,

840
00:31:48,220 --> 00:31:48,920
wait a second.

841
00:31:48,920 --> 00:31:50,180
Let me write this down.

842
00:31:54,310 --> 00:31:55,270
He told me

843
00:31:56,380 --> 00:31:57,310
his grandmother kept pestering him

844
00:31:57,310 --> 00:31:58,140
to find a wife.

845
00:31:59,920 --> 00:32:01,520
Before going into the mountains,

846
00:32:01,520 --> 00:32:03,250
she found a pretty girl for him.

847
00:32:04,140 --> 00:32:05,200
He was supposed to go meet her

848
00:32:05,200 --> 00:32:06,400
when coming back out.

849
00:32:08,880 --> 00:32:10,240
He was only 18.

850
00:32:11,820 --> 00:32:12,850
If he were in a city,

851
00:32:12,850 --> 00:32:14,710
he'd probably still be in school.

852
00:32:14,820 --> 00:32:16,070
Why the rush to find a wife?

853
00:32:16,070 --> 00:32:16,650
Okay.

854
00:32:17,430 --> 00:32:18,000
Okay.

855
00:32:18,890 --> 00:32:19,820
This is so vivid.

856
00:32:24,630 --> 00:32:25,180
Sorry.

857
00:32:25,270 --> 00:32:26,690
Please, go on.

858
00:32:33,990 --> 00:32:34,940
That night...

859
00:32:36,820 --> 00:32:39,220
When the poachers' headlights flashed on,

860
00:32:39,630 --> 00:32:41,430
shining straight into his face,

861
00:32:43,100 --> 00:32:45,100
he was just like a Tibetan antelope.

862
00:32:45,330 --> 00:32:46,530
He froze completely.

863
00:32:48,330 --> 00:32:50,130
Just as he tried to raise his gun,

864
00:32:50,760 --> 00:32:51,690
he was shot dead.

865
00:32:58,350 --> 00:32:59,000
What?

866
00:32:59,980 --> 00:33:00,920
Different from the heroic,

867
00:33:00,920 --> 00:33:02,000
noble sacrifice

868
00:33:02,030 --> 00:33:02,830
you imagined?

869
00:33:04,590 --> 00:33:05,990
If you write it like that,

870
00:33:06,480 --> 00:33:06,980
would the newspaper

871
00:33:06,980 --> 00:33:07,780
lose readers?

872
00:33:09,030 --> 00:33:09,590
No...

873
00:33:13,480 --> 00:33:14,050
But this is

874
00:33:14,050 --> 00:33:14,440
what

875
00:33:14,460 --> 00:33:15,460
really happened.

876
00:33:17,090 --> 00:33:18,330
For you,

877
00:33:19,510 --> 00:33:20,790
glorifying suffering

878
00:33:21,910 --> 00:33:23,450
and using a young life

879
00:33:23,520 --> 00:33:25,110
to attract attention

880
00:33:25,940 --> 00:33:27,140
might be meaningful.

881
00:33:29,530 --> 00:33:30,640
But for us,

882
00:33:32,550 --> 00:33:34,280
this is a tragedy for a young man

883
00:33:34,510 --> 00:33:35,740
and a family.

884
00:33:37,290 --> 00:33:39,150
It means we failed to protect him.

885
00:33:45,900 --> 00:33:46,660
Out here,

886
00:33:48,070 --> 00:33:49,810
no one wants to trade their life

887
00:33:49,910 --> 00:33:51,240
for a poacher's life.

888
00:33:56,240 --> 00:33:56,720
We just want to

889
00:33:56,720 --> 00:33:57,920
survive as best we can

890
00:33:59,780 --> 00:34:00,840
and do our job well.

891
00:34:07,110 --> 00:34:07,940
That was

892
00:34:08,800 --> 00:34:09,670
very well said.

893
00:34:10,960 --> 00:34:11,900
People who haven't been through it

894
00:34:11,900 --> 00:34:13,500
wouldn't be able to say this.

895
00:34:13,590 --> 00:34:14,030
Officer Bai,

896
00:34:14,030 --> 00:34:15,420
can you say a bit more?

897
00:34:15,510 --> 00:34:16,710
Just speak your mind.

898
00:34:17,150 --> 00:34:17,670
Let's just chat

899
00:34:17,670 --> 00:34:18,540
like friends.

900
00:34:19,650 --> 00:34:20,210
Okay.

901
00:34:21,230 --> 00:34:22,260
Then I'll say one more thing.

902
00:34:22,260 --> 00:34:23,150
You can say more.

903
00:34:23,150 --> 00:34:24,150
Don't hold back.

904
00:34:26,350 --> 00:34:27,000
Everyone hopes

905
00:34:27,000 --> 00:34:28,330
you'll leave here soon.

906
00:34:30,409 --> 00:34:31,210
Including me.

907
00:34:32,250 --> 00:34:33,520
Stop following us.

908
00:34:34,530 --> 00:34:34,989
The Mountain Patrol

909
00:34:34,989 --> 00:34:36,320
isn't the place for you.

910
00:34:39,830 --> 00:34:40,500
Why?

911
00:34:41,800 --> 00:34:42,880
Because out there,

912
00:34:43,760 --> 00:34:44,260
everyone's

913
00:34:44,260 --> 00:34:45,860
first reaction to seeing you

914
00:34:46,139 --> 00:34:46,850
is worry.

915
00:34:47,000 --> 00:34:48,500
It's not like I haven't been
into the mountains.

916
00:34:48,500 --> 00:34:49,630
I've been living with you guys

917
00:34:49,630 --> 00:34:50,340
for so long.

918
00:34:50,800 --> 00:34:51,510
I've never

919
00:34:51,530 --> 00:34:52,790
dropped the ball, have I?

920
00:34:52,790 --> 00:34:54,350
It's a tough job.

921
00:34:55,510 --> 00:34:57,440
Never mind running into poachers.

922
00:34:58,350 --> 00:34:59,960
Just a sandstorm

923
00:35:01,100 --> 00:35:02,230
or a bout of dysentery

924
00:35:02,230 --> 00:35:03,140
could kill you.

925
00:35:05,210 --> 00:35:06,760
It's not a heroic way to die.

926
00:35:07,960 --> 00:35:08,480
I think

927
00:35:08,930 --> 00:35:09,350
you should just

928
00:35:09,350 --> 00:35:10,880
go back where you came from.

929
00:35:11,670 --> 00:35:12,730
Be a good reporter.

930
00:35:13,740 --> 00:35:15,740
There are plenty of stories to write

931
00:35:16,060 --> 00:35:17,520
and plenty of things to do.

932
00:35:18,970 --> 00:35:19,900
Don't you think?

933
00:35:26,410 --> 00:35:27,510
I've said too much.

934
00:35:35,820 --> 00:35:36,730
Officer Bai Ju,

935
00:35:39,150 --> 00:35:39,570
thank you

936
00:35:39,570 --> 00:35:40,900
for telling me all that.

937
00:35:41,340 --> 00:35:42,400
But I'm a reporter.

938
00:35:43,060 --> 00:35:43,670
If I see something,

939
00:35:43,670 --> 00:35:45,070
I can't pretend I didn't.

940
00:35:45,470 --> 00:35:47,000
It's professional ethics.

941
00:35:49,830 --> 00:35:50,680
I've decided.

942
00:35:51,540 --> 00:35:52,870
I'm staying here.

943
00:35:54,200 --> 00:35:54,880
So,

944
00:35:57,810 --> 00:35:59,410
can you teach me how to shoot?

945
00:36:08,240 --> 00:36:09,640
As for shooting stances,

946
00:36:10,000 --> 00:36:11,060
besides standing,

947
00:36:11,220 --> 00:36:12,820
there's prone and kneeling.

948
00:36:13,760 --> 00:36:14,780
But one thing never changes—

949
00:36:14,780 --> 00:36:16,840
you use your hands and feet together.

950
00:36:17,110 --> 00:36:18,190
What did I just tell you?

951
00:36:18,190 --> 00:36:18,920
Look at you.

952
00:36:19,660 --> 00:36:21,410
Keep your feet shoulder-width apart

953
00:36:21,410 --> 00:36:22,830
or slightly narrower.

954
00:36:23,810 --> 00:36:25,180
Keep your feet parallel

955
00:36:25,200 --> 00:36:27,030
with toes pointing slightly out.

956
00:36:27,030 --> 00:36:29,360
Keep your weight on
the balls of your feet.

957
00:36:30,160 --> 00:36:31,080
I am.

958
00:36:32,830 --> 00:36:33,960
How long has it been?

959
00:36:34,260 --> 00:36:35,590
It's only been a minute.

960
00:36:36,050 --> 00:36:37,870
Don't hunch your right shoulder.

961
00:36:37,870 --> 00:36:38,230
Your muscles

962
00:36:38,230 --> 00:36:39,440
will get too tense.

963
00:36:39,730 --> 00:36:40,630
Even without that,

964
00:36:40,630 --> 00:36:41,620
I already feel

965
00:36:41,650 --> 00:36:43,240
my muscles tensing up.

966
00:36:44,700 --> 00:36:45,190
Didn't you say

967
00:36:45,190 --> 00:36:46,730
you hold a camera all day?

968
00:36:46,840 --> 00:36:47,780
Isn't your arm strength good?

969
00:36:47,780 --> 00:36:48,800
I use two hands for the camera.

970
00:36:48,800 --> 00:36:49,480
This is one-handed.

971
00:36:49,480 --> 00:36:50,730
How is that the same?

972
00:36:51,300 --> 00:36:52,230
How much longer?

973
00:36:54,730 --> 00:36:55,630
In our shooting training,

974
00:36:55,630 --> 00:36:56,350
if you can't last five minutes,

975
00:36:56,350 --> 00:36:58,080
you don't deserve to hold a gun.

976
00:36:59,150 --> 00:37:00,210
What are you doing?

977
00:37:00,380 --> 00:37:01,080
Hold it up.

978
00:37:02,800 --> 00:37:05,600
-I can't take it anymore.
-You've barely started.

979
00:37:08,030 --> 00:37:09,680
Just looking at your stance

980
00:37:09,820 --> 00:37:10,800
pisses me off.

981
00:37:11,900 --> 00:37:13,460
Look at how you're standing.

982
00:37:13,460 --> 00:37:14,030
Just like you—

983
00:37:14,030 --> 00:37:15,360
Push your hips forward.

984
00:37:15,510 --> 00:37:16,830
Stick your lower belly out.

985
00:37:16,830 --> 00:37:17,230
Arch your back.

986
00:37:17,230 --> 00:37:18,290
What are you doing?

987
00:37:18,920 --> 00:37:19,980
What are you doing?

988
00:37:20,380 --> 00:37:20,800
I...

989
00:37:21,440 --> 00:37:22,920
-I…
-I'm teaching you.

990
00:37:23,530 --> 00:37:24,650
If you don't cooperate,

991
00:37:24,650 --> 00:37:26,130
I'll let He Qingyuan teach you.

992
00:37:26,130 --> 00:37:27,090
I'll cooperate.

993
00:37:27,210 --> 00:37:28,030
Come on.

994
00:37:28,130 --> 00:37:29,030
Come on for what?

995
00:37:29,030 --> 00:37:30,030
Hold it yourself.

996
00:37:31,000 --> 00:37:32,650
Hold it for five minutes first.

997
00:37:32,650 --> 00:37:33,170
I'll reset the timer.

998
00:37:33,170 --> 00:37:33,920
The last part didn't count.

999
00:37:33,920 --> 00:37:35,270
I already held it for a minute.

1000
00:37:35,270 --> 00:37:36,200
Keep holding it.

1001
00:37:40,720 --> 00:37:41,900
You're a grown man,

1002
00:37:42,680 --> 00:37:43,820
but you're so weak.

1003
00:37:55,240 --> 00:37:56,970
Why isn't it getting better?

1004
00:38:01,040 --> 00:38:01,730
The medicine I prescribed,

1005
00:38:01,730 --> 00:38:02,990
did you take it on time?

1006
00:38:03,360 --> 00:38:03,940
Yes.

1007
00:38:04,430 --> 00:38:05,760
I still don't feel well.

1008
00:38:07,380 --> 00:38:09,110
Did you use the menstrual belt?

1009
00:38:09,450 --> 00:38:10,020
Yes.

1010
00:38:12,030 --> 00:38:13,430
What about toilet paper?

1011
00:38:13,720 --> 00:38:15,520
Did you use toilet paper with it?

1012
00:38:18,070 --> 00:38:18,880
Well...

1013
00:38:21,110 --> 00:38:22,510
I didn't want to use that.

1014
00:38:22,530 --> 00:38:23,840
I used wool instead.

1015
00:38:24,440 --> 00:38:25,420
Cairen,

1016
00:38:25,510 --> 00:38:26,690
you can't use wool anymore.

1017
00:38:26,690 --> 00:38:27,880
Why won't you listen to me?

1018
00:38:27,880 --> 00:38:28,480
Well,

1019
00:38:28,500 --> 00:38:30,230
toilet paper is too expensive.

1020
00:38:30,270 --> 00:38:31,850
Besides, if I take it home,

1021
00:38:31,980 --> 00:38:33,230
and Duojie and Zhaxi see it,

1022
00:38:33,230 --> 00:38:34,290
they'll use it too.

1023
00:38:34,550 --> 00:38:35,670
I didn't tell them.

1024
00:38:35,800 --> 00:38:36,340
They're family.

1025
00:38:36,340 --> 00:38:37,670
Why can't you tell them?

1026
00:38:38,110 --> 00:38:39,390
It's a health issue.

1027
00:38:39,410 --> 00:38:40,780
There's nothing to be ashamed of.

1028
00:38:40,780 --> 00:38:41,870
You have to tell them.

1029
00:38:41,870 --> 00:38:42,370
Okay.

1030
00:38:43,490 --> 00:38:44,890
If you keep ignoring this

1031
00:38:45,000 --> 00:38:46,030
and get an ascending infection,

1032
00:38:46,030 --> 00:38:47,320
it will be serious.

1033
00:38:49,920 --> 00:38:50,500
I see.

1034
00:38:51,380 --> 00:38:52,590
Brother, come here.

1035
00:38:52,620 --> 00:38:53,890
There's a vendor here.

1036
00:38:53,910 --> 00:38:54,940
All right.

1037
00:38:56,030 --> 00:38:59,400
How is this one? Does it look good?

1038
00:38:59,490 --> 00:39:01,090
It really is a nice necklace.

1039
00:39:01,880 --> 00:39:03,680
But it's too expensive.

1040
00:39:03,820 --> 00:39:05,070
Who can afford this?

1041
00:39:06,080 --> 00:39:09,730
This turquoise is high quality.

1042
00:39:09,880 --> 00:39:12,880
It's already very cheap.

1043
00:39:13,330 --> 00:39:14,390
I... I'm saying...

1044
00:39:14,410 --> 00:39:16,080
the price of this necklace,

1045
00:39:17,050 --> 00:39:18,240
can you go any lower?

1046
00:39:18,340 --> 00:39:20,470
It's just too expensive.

1047
00:39:20,650 --> 00:39:21,510
Too expensive.

1048
00:39:21,800 --> 00:39:22,670
No, no.

1049
00:39:23,610 --> 00:39:25,110
It's worn on the neck,

1050
00:39:26,300 --> 00:39:27,780
not on the head.

1051
00:39:28,320 --> 00:39:29,340
I... I know that.

1052
00:39:29,360 --> 00:39:30,530
I know this necklace

1053
00:39:30,570 --> 00:39:32,090
is worn on the neck.

1054
00:39:32,290 --> 00:39:33,130
I mean, for this necklace,

1055
00:39:33,130 --> 00:39:34,010
the price...

1056
00:39:34,300 --> 00:39:34,980
the price,

1057
00:39:35,040 --> 00:39:36,270
can it be lower?

1058
00:39:36,610 --> 00:39:37,960
Lower the price.

1059
00:39:38,360 --> 00:39:38,840
Look,

1060
00:39:39,400 --> 00:39:41,230
wearing it on the wrist like this

1061
00:39:41,320 --> 00:39:42,760
also works.

1062
00:39:47,710 --> 00:39:48,260
Zhaxi,

1063
00:39:48,670 --> 00:39:49,530
don't just stand there watching.

1064
00:39:49,530 --> 00:39:50,730
Say something for me.

1065
00:39:50,850 --> 00:39:51,730
Help me...

1066
00:39:51,840 --> 00:39:52,380
Zhaxi,

1067
00:39:52,860 --> 00:39:53,990
why are you running?

1068
00:39:54,550 --> 00:39:55,030
Zhaxi!

1069
00:39:55,590 --> 00:39:57,120
Why are you running, Zhaxi?

1070
00:39:59,520 --> 00:40:01,230
Why are you running?

1071
00:40:01,860 --> 00:40:02,590
Why?

1072
00:40:05,800 --> 00:40:07,260
You can't speak Mandarin?

1073
00:40:07,360 --> 00:40:08,340
Of course I can.

1074
00:40:09,020 --> 00:40:10,220
My Mandarin is great.

1075
00:40:11,330 --> 00:40:12,930
Then why are you avoiding me?

1076
00:40:12,960 --> 00:40:14,180
I didn't mess with you.

1077
00:40:14,180 --> 00:40:15,130
Mom said

1078
00:40:15,710 --> 00:40:16,520
you're a bad guy who goes into

1079
00:40:16,520 --> 00:40:18,780
the Uninhabited Zone to hunt antelopes.

1080
00:40:21,150 --> 00:40:23,150
Your mom got the wrong idea about me.

1081
00:40:23,540 --> 00:40:24,600
I'm a decent person.

1082
00:40:24,600 --> 00:40:27,000
I have absolutely never hunted antelopes.

1083
00:40:28,390 --> 00:40:29,140
I swear.

1084
00:40:30,780 --> 00:40:31,380
I swear,

1085
00:40:31,400 --> 00:40:32,340
I swear to Buddha,

1086
00:40:32,340 --> 00:40:33,530
I have absolutely never hunted antelopes.

1087
00:40:33,530 --> 00:40:34,980
Then why are you buying necklaces?

1088
00:40:34,980 --> 00:40:35,430
I...

1089
00:40:37,710 --> 00:40:38,210
I'm buying necklaces

1090
00:40:38,210 --> 00:40:39,460
to do a good deed.

1091
00:40:40,820 --> 00:40:41,810
I buy them

1092
00:40:41,840 --> 00:40:42,700
from herdsmen,

1093
00:40:43,030 --> 00:40:44,360
and then I resell them.

1094
00:40:44,910 --> 00:40:45,230
I am

1095
00:40:45,260 --> 00:40:47,520
promoting traditional Tibetan culture

1096
00:40:47,630 --> 00:40:49,560
and fostering ethnic friendship.

1097
00:40:49,840 --> 00:40:50,940
Stop lying.

1098
00:40:50,970 --> 00:40:52,650
You just want to make money.

1099
00:40:54,500 --> 00:40:56,230
Who doesn't want to make money?

1100
00:40:56,320 --> 00:40:57,300
Don't you?

1101
00:41:01,870 --> 00:41:02,710
How about this?

1102
00:41:02,710 --> 00:41:04,190
You translate for me,

1103
00:41:04,240 --> 00:41:05,300
and when it's done,

1104
00:41:05,560 --> 00:41:06,620
I'll give you a cut.

1105
00:41:09,050 --> 00:41:10,180
Really?

1106
00:41:10,350 --> 00:41:10,930
Really.

1107
00:41:11,620 --> 00:41:12,880
I'll give you one yuan.

1108
00:41:13,030 --> 00:41:14,960
You'll get it once the deal is made.

1109
00:41:16,300 --> 00:41:16,830
Let's go.

1110
00:41:17,520 --> 00:41:18,530
Help me talk to him.

1111
00:41:18,530 --> 00:41:19,990
Ask him to sell it cheaper.

1112
00:41:23,520 --> 00:41:25,120
Do you have anything better?

1113
00:41:25,320 --> 00:41:27,180
It's okay if it's more expensive.

1114
00:41:27,460 --> 00:41:28,760
We all use this.

1115
00:41:28,790 --> 00:41:30,390
This is the best straw paper.

1116
00:41:32,070 --> 00:41:33,500
Do you have that...

1117
00:41:34,320 --> 00:41:35,300
finer kind?

1118
00:41:35,710 --> 00:41:37,480
The soft, white toilet paper?

1119
00:41:38,480 --> 00:41:39,810
We don't have that here.

1120
00:41:40,450 --> 00:41:41,780
Bigger stores

1121
00:41:41,910 --> 00:41:42,710
might have it.

1122
00:41:42,920 --> 00:41:44,260
Why don't you sell it?

1123
00:41:44,980 --> 00:41:45,960
Too expensive.

1124
00:41:46,820 --> 00:41:47,730
No one buys it.

1125
00:41:48,220 --> 00:41:49,070
Even in big stores,

1126
00:41:49,070 --> 00:41:50,760
not many people buy it.

1127
00:41:54,970 --> 00:41:56,100
I'll take this then.

1128
00:41:57,530 --> 00:41:58,630
Get me ten bundles.

1129
00:41:58,860 --> 00:41:59,320
Okay.

1130
00:42:09,360 --> 00:42:10,400
Make it five.

1131
00:42:20,050 --> 00:42:20,690
Mom.

1132
00:42:21,700 --> 00:42:22,800
You're back early.

1133
00:42:25,530 --> 00:42:25,780
You...

1134
00:42:25,780 --> 00:42:26,780
How did you get in?

1135
00:42:26,880 --> 00:42:27,230
Well...

1136
00:42:27,230 --> 00:42:28,830
the key was on the doorframe.

1137
00:42:29,640 --> 00:42:30,730
Zhacuo told me.

1138
00:42:31,960 --> 00:42:32,430
Don't you know to knock

1139
00:42:32,430 --> 00:42:33,490
before you come in?

1140
00:42:33,880 --> 00:42:34,570
Zhacuo told me...

1141
00:42:34,570 --> 00:42:35,610
he said just open the door,

1142
00:42:35,610 --> 00:42:36,320
come in and cook.

1143
00:42:36,320 --> 00:42:36,860
That's the rule.

1144
00:42:36,860 --> 00:42:37,460
What rule?

1145
00:42:37,570 --> 00:42:38,070
Aren't you supposed to knock

1146
00:42:38,070 --> 00:42:39,070
before entering?

1147
00:42:42,260 --> 00:42:42,820
Yeah?

1148
00:42:43,170 --> 00:42:44,340
I-I didn't know.

1149
00:42:44,480 --> 00:42:45,260
I'm sorry.

1150
00:42:46,010 --> 00:42:47,870
I'll definitely knock next time.

1151
00:42:48,570 --> 00:42:49,230
Because...

1152
00:42:49,280 --> 00:42:50,280
when Zhacuo told me,

1153
00:42:50,280 --> 00:42:50,900
I was wondering about it.

1154
00:42:50,900 --> 00:42:51,500
I thought,

1155
00:42:51,820 --> 00:42:53,280
your family rules are quite strange.

1156
00:42:53,280 --> 00:42:56,340
-If bad guys wanted to come in…
-What are you doing here?

1157
00:42:58,020 --> 00:42:59,150
To bring you photos.

1158
00:43:00,880 --> 00:43:02,210
I didn't take any photo.

1159
00:43:02,550 --> 00:43:04,610
I took candid shots in the mountains.

1160
00:43:05,270 --> 00:43:06,730
I just got them developed.

1161
00:43:07,230 --> 00:43:07,690
Thanks.

1162
00:43:07,970 --> 00:43:08,470
Now go.
